'''Chewbacca's family''' was the extended family of the [[Wookiee]] [[Chewbacca]] on [[Kashyyyk]], whose members included his father [[Attichitcuk]], his son [[Lumpawaroo]] and his [[Marriage|wife]] [[Mallatobuck]]. Following the [[Liberation of Kashyyyk|liberation]] of Kashyyyk from the [[Galactic Empire]]'s grasp, Chewbacca finally reunited with his family.

==History==
===Early members===
A [[Wookiee]] [[Gender|male]] named [[Attichitcuk]]<ref name="Solo Junior Novel">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: A Junior Novel]]''</ref> and a [[Chewbacca's mother|Wookiee female]]<ref name="Visual Dictionary">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary, New Edition]]''</ref> [[Reproduction|gave birth]] to a son named [[Chewbacca]].<ref name="Solo Junior Novel" />

===Enslavement and separation===
{{Quote|Hey, you're the married one. Find me a human girl with Malla's brains and silky hair and maybe I'll consider it.|Han Solo, to Chewbacca|<ref name="PSFB">''[[A New Hope: The Princess, the Scoundrel, and the Farm Boy]]''</ref>}}
[[File:ChewbaccaFamily.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Chewbacca, Malla and Lumpawaroo]]
Chewbacca had a wife named [[Mallatobuck]]<ref name="PSFB" /> and a son named [[Lumpawaroo]].<ref name="Empire's End">''[[Aftermath: Empire's End]]''</ref> During the [[Imperial Era]], Chewbacca was [[Slavery|enslaved]] by [[Trandoshan]]s.<ref name="Chewbacca II">[[Chewbacca (2015) 2|''Chewbacca'' (2015) 2]]</ref> "Malla" and their son "Waroo" were also enslaved by the [[Galactic Empire]] and were put into an Imperial slave labor camp on their [[homeworld]] of [[Kashyyyk]].<ref name="AB Update">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know, Updated and Expanded]]''</ref> Waroo was eventually separated from his mother and forced to work as a slave at [[Commandant]] [[Dessard]]'s labor camp on the slopes of [[Mount Arayakyak]].<ref name="Empire's End" /> Meanwhile, Chewbacca was forced to cut [[wroshyr tree]]s in order to feed the [[Imperial Army]].<ref name="Aftermath">[[Aftermath (novel)|''Aftermath'']]</ref>

===Chewbacca's life debt===
{{Quote|What's your name, anyway?''"<br />«''Chewbacca, son of Attichitcuk.''»<br />"''All right. Well, you're gonna need a nickname, 'cause I ain't saying that every time.|Han Solo and Chewbacca, soon after meeting|<ref name="Solo Junior Novel" />}}
Chewbacca eventually ended up at an Imperial Army frontline base on the [[Expansion Region]] world of [[Mimban]], where he was "fed" prisoners and gained the nickname "the beast." When the [[swamp trooper]] [[Han Solo]] was thrown into Chewbacca's pen for desertion, Solo managed to convince Chewbacca to help him escape together. The two subsequently joined [[Tobias Beckett]]'s [[Beckett's gang|gang]] and were involved in several adventures that brought them into conflict with the [[Crimson Dawn]] and [[Cloud-Riders]].<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref> Out of gratitude for freeing him from the Empire, Chewie swore a [[life debt]] to Solo.<ref name="AB 1st">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know]]''</ref>

By [[0 ABY]], Chewbacca and Han Solo had joined the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] after rescuing [[Princess]] [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Leia Organa]] and helping transport the [[Death Star plans]] to the rebel base on Yavin 4.<ref name="Episode IV">{{Film|IV}}</ref> Over the next four years, Chewbacca remained by Han Solo's side and accompanied him on a series of adventures that brought them to [[Hoth]], the [[Anoat system]], and [[Cloud City]]. After Solo was frozen in [[carbonite]] and taken by the [[bounty hunter]] [[Boba Fett]] to [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure]], Chewbacca accompanied [[Landonis Balthazar Calrissian|Lando Calrissian]] on a [[Rescue of Han Solo|mission to rescue Han Solo]], honoring his life debt to Han.<ref name="Episode V">{{Film|V}}</ref>

Chewbacca helped Princess Leia, Lando, [[Luke Skywalker]], [[R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO]] rescue Han Solo on [[Tatooine]], resulting in the [[death]] of Jabba at the [[Great Pit of Carkoon]]. Chewbacca subsequently took part in the [[Battle of Endor]] and helped seize the [[DS-2 Death Star II Mobile Battle Station|second Death Star's]] [[Death Star's shield generator|shield generator]] on [[Endor]].<ref name="Episode VI">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

===Return to Kashyyyk===
Out of respect of Chewbacca's life debt to him, Han agreed to help the Wookiee liberate his homeworld of Kashyyyk in the months after the Battle of Endor, which saw the death of [[Darth Sidious|the Emperor]], the disintegration of the Empire, and the transformation of the Rebel Alliance into the [[New Republic]].<ref name="Aftermath" /> While trying to recruit smugglers and Wookiee exiles, Chewbacca was recaptured by Imperial forces in [[5 ABY]] and imprisoned at [[Ashmead's Lock]] [[prison]] on Kashyyyk. With the help of [[Norra Wexley]] and her [[Norra Wexley's team|team]], Solo managed to free Chewbacca and numerous rebel prisoners from Ashmead's Lock.<ref name="Life Debt">''[[Aftermath: Life Debt]]''</ref>

Working together with the former Imperial [[loyalty officer]] [[Sinjir Rath Velus]], the bounty hunter [[Jas Emari]], the New Republic commando [[Jom Barell]] along with several Wookiee exiles and former slaves, Han and Chewbacca attacked [[Grand Moff]] [[Lozen Tolruck]]'s [[Lozen Tolruck's island fortress|island fortress]] and disabled the [[Behavioral modification biochip|inhibitor chips]] that kept the Wookiees enslaved. The Wookiees subsequently rebelled in a [[Liberation of Kashyyyk|planet-wide uprising]] that was aided by the New Republic. While Han left to rejoin Princess Leia, Chewbacca stayed behind on Kashyyyk to liberate his family.<ref name="Life Debt" />

While taking part in a joint Wookiee-New Republic mopping-up operation, Chewbacca rescued his son Waroo from Commandant Dessard. Chewbacca experienced an emotional reunion with his son.<ref name="Empire's End" /> Chewbacca also reunited with his wife, Malla, following Kashyyyk's liberation.<ref name="AB Update" />

===New Republic era and beyond===
In the years following the [[Battle of Jakku]], Chewbacca reestablished connections with his family.<ref name="TFAVD">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> Chewbacca also kept in touch with his old friend Han Solo, who had become the owner of a shipping company and the manager of a series of racing championships known as the [[Five Sabers]]. Chewie also kept in touch with Princess Leia, who had become a New Republic senator. Chewie expressed support for Leia following the [[Napkin Bombing]] and the public outcry resulting from revelations of Leia's true parentage as the daughter of [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]].<ref name="Bloodline">[[Bloodline (novel)|''Bloodline'']]</ref>

Despite his peaceful retirement, Chewbacca decided to renew his bond with Han Solo when the latter resumed his smuggling activities. As a Wookiee, Chewie's strong familial bonds and extended lifespan enabled him to spend decades away from his people.<ref name="TFAVD" /> In [[34 ABY]], Chewbacca and Solo encountered the scavenger [[Rey Skywalker|Rey]], the former [[First Order]] [[First Order stormtrooper|stormtrooper]] [[Finn]], and the [[droid]] [[BB-8]]. As a result, the two became drawn into the [[First Order-Resistance War|conflict]] between General Organa's [[Resistance]] and the First Order, an Imperial remnant devoted to restoring Imperial rule over [[the galaxy]]. Chewbacca experienced a major personal loss when his longtime friend Han Solo was killed by his estranged son [[Ben Solo|Kylo Ren]].<ref name="Episode VII">{{Film|VII}}</ref>

Following the [[Battle of Starkiller Base]], Chewbacca accompanied Rey to the [[Unknown Regions]] world of [[Ahch-To]], where Luke Skywalker had retreated to. Chewie and Rey also helped evacuate General Organa and the surviving remnants of the Resistance during the [[Battle of Crait]].<ref name="Episode VIII">{{Film|VIII}}</ref>

Chewbacca's family was remembered long after the [[Galactic Civil War]]. After a [[Unidentified Whill|member]] of the [[Whills]], who was writing the [[Journal of the Whills]], became irritated by the constant interruptions of a [[Unidentified second Whill|fellow Whill]], the other Whill resolved to write an episode about how the Wookiee's family celebrated [[Life Day]].<ref name="Whills" />

